module [v3d]

\ 3D vector type for the Supershow 3D pack.
\
\ A v3d is three contiguous 32-bit float cells: x, y, z.  Declare one as a
\ NIBS property with `v3d-prop name` (the `:v3d` type lives in forge/nibs.vfx),
\ or as a standalone scratch buffer with `create name s/v3d allot`.
\
\ Vectors live in memory.  To compute, pull the triple onto the DATA stack with
\ `3@` -- the cells carry IEEE-float bit patterns untouched -- operate, then
\ `3!` back.  The arithmetic words (`3+`, `3-`, `3negate`) move each component
\ through the x87 stack two operands at a time via `sf>f`/`f>sf`, so the float
\ stack is never more than ~2 slots deep regardless of how many vectors are in
\ flight.  Slower than native fixed-point adds, but it sidesteps both the 16.16
\ overflow ceiling and the x87's 8-slot depth limit.

\ TODO: optimize with SSE2 instructions

public

3 cells constant s/v3d

\ --- component field-address accessors ( v3d - field-addr ) ---
\ Named v3d.x/.y/.z, NOT >x/>y/>z: the latter would silently shadow the address
\ accessors the %xy trait defines. Use these when you need a component's address
\ (e.g. al_transform_coordinates_3d's float* args); for values use z@/z!.
: v3d.x  ( v3d - a )  ;
: v3d.y  ( v3d - a )  cell+ ;
: v3d.z  ( v3d - a )  2 cells + ;

\ --- scalar access ( the cells hold float bits ) ---
: z@  ( addr - z )  2 cells + @ ;
: z!  ( z addr - )  2 cells + ! ;

\ --- whole-triple moves (plain cell copies; float bits ride along) ---
: 3@  ( addr - x y z )  dup @  over cell+ @  rot 2 cells + @ ;
: 3!  ( x y z addr - )  >r  r@ 2 cells + !  r@ cell+ !  r> ! ;

\ --- bridges to/from the float stack (for Allegro calls), z ends on top ---
: 3sf@  ( addr - ) ( f: - x y z )  dup sf@  dup cell+ sf@  2 cells + sf@ ;
: 3sf!  ( addr - ) ( f: x y z - )  >r  r@ 2 cells + sf!  r@ cell+ sf!  r> sf! ;

\ --- build a vector from three integers ---
: s>v3  ( ix iy iz addr - )
    {: ix iy iz addr :}
    ix s>f  iy s>f  iz s>f  addr 3sf! ;

\ --- arithmetic on triples sitting on the data stack ---
: 3+  ( x1 y1 z1 x2 y2 z2 - x3 y3 z3 )
    {: x1 y1 z1 x2 y2 z2 :}
    x1 sf>f x2 sf>f f+ f>sf
    y1 sf>f y2 sf>f f+ f>sf
    z1 sf>f z2 sf>f f+ f>sf ;

: 3-  ( x1 y1 z1 x2 y2 z2 - x3 y3 z3 )
    {: x1 y1 z1 x2 y2 z2 :}
    x1 sf>f x2 sf>f f- f>sf
    y1 sf>f y2 sf>f f- f>sf
    z1 sf>f z2 sf>f f- f>sf ;

: 3negate  ( x y z - -x -y -z )
    {: x1 y1 z1 :}
    x1 sf>f fnegate f>sf
    y1 sf>f fnegate f>sf
    z1 sf>f fnegate f>sf ;

\ --- accumulate a triple into the vector at addr ---
: 3+!  ( x y z addr - )  dup >r 3@ 3+ r> 3! ;
